<subSubSection pageId="107" pageNumber="108" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="107.[151,1437,1693,1934]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1801,1826]" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Notes.</emphasis>
The nesting biology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1837" box="[558,666,1801,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[558,581,1802,1825]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[598,666,1801,1826]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[708,789,1802,1825]" country="United States of America" name="Kansas" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Kansas</collectingRegion>
has been studied in detail (
<bibRefCitation author="Michener" box="[1114,1293,1801,1826]" firstAuthor="Michener" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="1659 - 1748" refId="ref95128" refString="Michener, C. D. (1953) The biology of a leafcutter bee (Megachile brevis) and its associates. The University of Kansas Science Bulletin, 35, 1659 - 1748." type="journal article" year="1953">Michener 1953</bibRefCitation>
). Additional studies of this cavity and stem-nester are available from 
<collectingRegion box="[839,920,1838,1861]" country="United States of America" name="Kansas" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Kansas</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Baker" box="[940,1157,1837,1862]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Baker" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="290 - 313" refId="ref82789" refString="Baker, J. R., Kuhn, E. D. &amp; Bambara, S. B. (1985) Nests and immature stages of leafcutter bees (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae). Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 58, 290 - 313." type="journal article" year="1985">
Baker 
<emphasis box="[1022,1085,1837,1862]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">et al.</emphasis>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[1183,1283,1837,1862]" country="United States of America" name="Missouri" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Missouri</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rau" box="[1304,1424,1838,1862]" firstAuthor="Rau" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="219 - 224" refId="ref99779" refString="Rau, P. (1934) Notes on the behavior of certain solitary and social bees. Transactions of the Academy of Science of St. Louis, 28, 219 - 224." type="journal article" year="1934">Rau 1934</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingRegion box="[151,268,1873,1898]" country="United States of America" name="Wisconsin" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Wisconsin</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Medler &amp; Lussenhop" box="[283,590,1873,1898]" firstAuthor="Medler" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="1 - 80" refId="ref94805" refString="Medler, J. T. &amp; Lussenhop, J. F. (1968) Leafcutter bees of Wisconsin. University of Wisconsin Research Bulletin, 274, 1 - 80." type="journal article" year="1968">Medler &amp; Lussenhop 1968</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<collectingRegion box="[658,742,1874,1898]" country="United States of America" name="Oregon" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Oregon</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rockwood" box="[757,947,1873,1898]" firstAuthor="Rockwood" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="149 - 156" refId="ref100977" refString="Rockwood, L. P. (1951) Notes on insects associated with Lupinus polyphyllus Lindl. in the Pacific Northwest. Psyche, 27, 149 - 156." type="journal article" year="1951">Rockwood 1951</bibRefCitation>
). The latter may pertain to 
<taxonomicName authority="Cockerell" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="onobrychidis">
<emphasis box="[1252,1436,1873,1898]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">M. onobrychidis</emphasis>
Cockerell
</taxonomicName>
, which was formerly considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1837" box="[809,914,1909,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Megachile" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis">
<emphasis box="[809,914,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">M. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Sheffield" box="[973,1203,1909,1934]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Sheffield" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="29 - 43" refId="ref102251" refString="Sheffield, C. S., Dumesh, S. &amp; Cheryomina, M. (2011 a) Hylaeus punctatus (Hymenoptera: Colletidae), a bee species new to Canada, with notes on other non-native species. Journal of the Entomological Society of Ontario, 142, 29 - 43." type="journal article" year="2011">
<collectingRegion box="[973,1075,1909,1934]" country="United Kingdom" name="Sheffield" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">Sheffield</collectingRegion>
<emphasis box="[1082,1139,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="107" pageNumber="108">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bzdyk" box="[1215,1356,1909,1934]" firstAuthor="Bzdyk" pageId="107" pageNumber="108" pagination="31 - 61" refId="ref84710" refString="Bzdyk, E. L. (2012) A revision of the Megachile subgenus Litomegachile Mitchell with an illustrated key and description of a new species (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae, Megachilini). Zookeys, 221, 31 - 61. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 221.3234" type="journal article" year="2012">Bzdyk 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
